Category":"formula"}},{"id":"acc-AccessibleLabelNeeded","messageStrings":{"issue":{"text":"Missing accessible label"}},"properties":{"howToFix":["Edit the accessible label property to describe the item."],"whyFix":"If there's no accessible text, people who can’t see the screen won't understand what’s in images and controls.","level":"Medium","componentType":"app","primaryCategory":"accessibility"}},{"id":"acc-TabIndexShouldBeDefinedForInteractiveControl","messageStrings":{"issue":{"text":"Missing tab stop"}},"properties":{"howToFix":["Set TabIndex to 0 or greater to ensure that interactive elements have a tab stop."],"whyFix":"People who use the keyboard with your app will not be able to access this element without a tab stop.","level":"Medium","componentType":"app","primaryCategory":"accessibility"}},{"id":"app-UnusedVariables","messageStrings":{"issue":{"text":"Unused variable"}},"properties":{"howToFix":["Remove the unused variable."],"whyFix":"This variable is declared but is not referenced by any control, so it is not needed.","componentType":"app","primaryCategory":"performance","level":"Medium"}},{"id":"app-UnusedMediaResources","messageStrings":{"issue":{"text":"Unused media files"}},"properties":{"howToFix":["Remove the unused media file in the Media pane."],"whyFix":"This media file is not referenced by any control formulas so it is not needed. Removing it will improve performance.","componentType":"app","primaryCategory":"performance","level":"Medium"}},{"id":"app-CrossScreenEventDependencies","messageStrings":{"issue":{"text":"Event rule references a control on another screen"}},"properties":{"howToFix":["Move the work to an event on the owning screen (for example, Screen.OnVisible), or pass state between screens using Navigate's context parameter or a global variable and react to it on the target screen."],"whyFix":"Event rules (such as OnStart, OnVisible, and OnSelect) that reference controls on other screens force those screens to load and initialize early, even if the user never navigates to them. This can noticeably slow app start-up and navigation.","componentType":"app","primaryCategory":"performance","level":"Medium"}},{"id":"app-CountRowsGalleryAllItems","messageStrings":{"issue":{"text":"Use AllItemsCount instead of CountRows with AllItems"}},"properties":{"howToFix":["Replace CountRows(Gallery.AllItems) with Gallery.AllItemsCount for better performance."],"whyFix":"Using CountRows with a gallery's AllItems property forces the creation of an output table containing a copy of the input data source and the current state of all child controls. This may force uninitialized rows to be initialized, consuming additional CPU cycles, memory, and potentially triggering row-level network requests.","componentType":"app","primaryCategory":"performance","level":"Medium"}}]}},"invocations":[{"executionSuccessful":true}],"columnKind":"utf16CodeUnits"}]}